  "title": "A diminishing population whose every cohort more than replaces itself",
  "abstract": "We observe that a dynamic population model can have period fertility that is always below replacement and cohort fertility that is always above replacement. We ask whether such a paradoxical population will get larger or smaller, and show that it must",
